<p>This is pretty neat! <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Though I have one small quibble as it stands:</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Entries:</span></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">The current challenge submissions are:</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><em>Contests</em> have entries submitted. <em>Challenges</em> have responses issued. Or at least I think that makes sense.. Anyhow, it seems open to misinterpretation as it's currently written.</span></p>
<p>I like that we have this hub, maintaining it starting now will make things easier if this challenge garners lots of response (already well on its way, it seems). I just wouldn't want anyone to think this is something official, or that these pieces are directly competing with each other, or that there's a deadline or any reason not to go ahead and write their own attempt.</p>
<p>E: Excellent! Also, I've added my tale to the list. Hard to tell with my work sometimes, but i think this'll stick.</p>

