														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3634037">
									

<p>Actually, there is a way to link to a specific item on the list. I should know, I used it to create the link for Mr. JHTT. Just edit the page and place the following</p>
<blockquote>
<p>[[#name]]</p>
</blockquote>
<p>before the object you want to link to. Obviously, substitute &quot;name&quot; with whatever word you want to use. Then when you want to link to it, and &quot;#name&quot; to the end of the link url. For example, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/log-of-anomalous-items">http://www.scp-wiki.net/log-of-anomalous-items</a> takes you to the Log of Anomalous Items, while <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/log-of-anomalous-items#jhtt">http://www.scp-wiki.net/log-of-anomalous-items#jhtt</a> will take you directly to Mr. Just Has The Tattoo.</p>
<p>EDIT: I forgot to add, this is also used to link to specific blocks of 100 on the series pages. Maybe I should have used that as an example instead of shamelessly self-promoting.</p>

